-r : makes it only look in this module and parents, not anywhere else
load_dotenv : makes the whole thing look for the .env file in this and parent directorys 
active virtual env: source "VENV NAME"/bin/activate
when you want to start a venv with a premade list of environments you can set up a .txt file that names them:
reqs.txt that would contain (for example)
msal 
requests
python-dotenv
//
then once your in your venv you run:
pip install -r reqs.txt
//
-r means read from file 
